g" aria-label="Mariya Joseph" class="chakra-avatar__initials css-1ebyn6">MJ</div></span><div class="chakra-stack css-chgbhg"><p class="chakra-text css-b2463j">Mariya Joseph</p><p class="chakra-text css-ni95y">2 years ago</p><div class="chakra-stack css-16kr8nk"><p class="chakra-text css-10zovpx">PostgreSQL</p></div></div></div><div class="chakra-wrap css-19ug521"><ul class="chakra-wrap__list css-19lo6pj"><div class="Markdown_reactMarkdown__X0aZ_"><p><strong>PLEASE UPVOTE</strong>! <em>Here's a step-by-step breakdown of the given SQL query:</em></p>
<p>Step 1: SELECT user_id, DATE_PART('day', MAX(post_date) - MIN(post_date)) AS days_between
The query starts with the SELECT statement, which specifies the columns to be included in the result. In this case, we want to retrieve the user_id and the number of days between posts.</p>
<p>Step 2: FROM posts
The FROM clause specifies the table from which we are retrieving the data. In this case, we are querying the "posts" table.</p>
<p>Step 3: WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM post_date) = '2021'
The WHERE clause is used to filter the rows based on a condition. Here, we are filtering the posts to consider only those made in the year 2021. The EXTRACT function is used to extract the year from the post_date column, and the condition checks if it is equal to '2021'.</p>
<p>Step 4: GROUP BY user_id
The GROUP BY clause is used to group the result set by a specific column or columns. Here, we are grouping the results by the user_id column. This allows us to perform aggregate functions on each group separately.</p>
<p>Step 5: HAVING COUNT(post_id) &gt; 1
The HAVING clause is used to filter the groups based on a condition after the grouping has been applied. In this case, we want to include only those groups where the count of post_id (number of posts) is greater than 1.</p>
<p>Putting it all together, the query retrieves the user IDs and the number of days between the earliest and latest posts for each user in the year 2021, excluding users who have made only one post.</p>
<pre><code>SELECT user_id,DATE_PART('day',MAX(post_date)-MIN(post_date)) AS days_between
FROM posts
WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM post_date)='2021'
GROUP BY user_id
HAVING COUNT(post_id)&gt;1
</code></pre></div></ul></div><div class="css-lxox7m"><div class="css-1qofolz"><div class="chakra-stack css-9hjtr8"><button type="button" class="chakra-button css-19khf33"><svg viewBox="0 0 14 12" focusable="false" class="chakra-icon css-6hvw10" stroke-width="1.5"><svg width="14" height="12" viewBox="0 0 14 12" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M6 11L1 6M1 6L6 1M1 6H13" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="strokeWidth" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></svg></button><p class="chakra-text css-35ezg3">9</p><button type="button" class="chakra-button css-1wvw69"><svg viewBox="0 0 14 12" focusable="false" class="chakra-icon css-1174pge" stroke-width="1.5"><svg width="14" height="12" viewBox="0 0 14 12" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M6 11L1 6M1 6L6 1M1 6H13" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="strokeWidth" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></svg></button></div><button type="button" class="chakra-button css-rt580z"><span class="chakra-button__icon css-1wh2kri"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 14" focusable="false" class="chakra-icon css-onkibi" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="16" height="14" viewBox="0 0 16 14" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M1.5 7.50667C1.5 8.57333 2.24867 9.50267 3.30467 9.658C4.01667 9.76267 4.73667 9.844 5.46333 9.90067C5.774 9.92533 6.05867 10.088 6.232 10.348L8 13L9.768 10.348C9.94133 10.088 10.226 9.92533 10.5367 9.90133C11.2633 9.844 11.9833 9.76267 12.6953 9.658C13.7513 9.50267 14.5 8.574 14.5 7.506V3.494C14.5 2.426 13.7513 1.49733 12.6953 1.342C11.1406 1.11381 9.57135 0.999507 8 1C6.40533 1 4.83733 1.11667 3.30467 1.342C2.24867 1.49733 1.5 2.42667 1.5 3.494V7.506V7.50667Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></svg></span><p class="chakra-text css-35ezg3">Reply</p></button><button type="button" class="chakra-button css-ckyald" hidden=""><span class="chakra-button__icon css-